## Decision records

Architecture decisions live in `{{ADR_DIR}}/`. Index: `{{ADR_DIR}}/README.md`.

- New decision → `/adr <title>`
- Past decisions are append-only. To change one, write a new ADR that
  supersedes it; do not edit the old.

## Workflow

- Non-trivial change → `/plan <task>` first. Plans live in `docs/plans/`.
- Mechanical work (renames, formatting, log/config edits) → `/grunt`.
- Closing a plan → `/done` (verifies steps and prompts for ADRs).

## Models policy

- Planning, ADR, closing → **Opus** (auto via slash command frontmatter).
- Implementation → **Sonnet** (run `/model sonnet` once per session).
- Mechanical / log / config edits → `/grunt` runs on **Haiku**.
- Override anytime with `/model <name>`.

## Hooks

Mode: `{{HOOK_MODE}}` (configured at `.claude/aims-mode`). Change with:
```
echo nudge > .claude/aims-mode    # warn only
echo block > .claude/aims-mode    # block source edits without active plan
```
The planning lock (`.claude/.planning-lock`) always blocks edits regardless
of mode — this is what makes `/plan` actually read-only.

## Memory tree

The repo carries a navigable memory layer under `docs/memory/` (see
`docs/adr/0007-tree-based-memory-with-auto-maintenance.md` for the
full design). It is a NAVIGATOR over `CLAUDE.md`, ADRs, plans, and
external memory — never a copy of them.

- `docs/memory/` is seeded during `/init-workflow` when you choose `full`
  (the default). If you chose `install-only`, run `/memory-init` once to
  seed it from a codebase scan.
- `/remember <note>` — file a note into the right leaf.
- The `PostToolUse` marker hook flips affected leaves to
  `dirty: true` after every Edit/Write. The `Stop` hook
  consolidates dirty leaves via an LLM call, but only when the
  throttle trips (5 dirty leaves OR 30 min since last
  consolidation). `SessionEnd` runs the same consolidation
  un-throttled if the CLI is actually closed.
- `/done` forces a consolidation regardless of throttle.
- To browse the tree manually: `cat docs/memory/README.md`, then any
  leaf under `docs/memory/<tag>/<name>.md`.

Project conventions (build/test, models, hooks, layout) stay in
CLAUDE.md; the tree references them via `claude_md_refs:`.
